</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR181:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR181"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              181-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 181</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 115</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to California Physical Education Week. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 18, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 181, Patel.
                          California Physical Education Week.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would proclaim May 1, 2026, to May 7, 2026, inclusive, as California Physical Education Week.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_D5263EB7-1C6E-4423-A6AA-F71347BF5FF7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, For purposes of this resolution, “physical education” includes both general physical education and adapted physical education; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A176206F-CEB9-4CFC-AFFA-3D7B88D0420C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Physical education is an academic discipline that equips California students with the knowledge, skills, and dispositions necessary to develop and maintain physical, mental, and social health throughout their lifespan; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0D84E756-8ADF-41E7-8E65-FC1A2BE7108A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Instruction in physical education contributes to pupil learning by supporting literacy development, social-emotional learning, positive school culture, and engagement across all content areas; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_01F6D1E8-4DF2-4484-93EB-FD5A9156137A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Physical education is an integral component of a well-rounded education in California and nationwide within the Every Student Succeeds Act, contributing to college, military, career, and vocational readiness and supporting a productive, healthy adulthood; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_AD41969F-1D4D-4F07-BD3F-F05FCFEFF2B4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Scientific evidence indicates that the components of physical fitness are associated with cognitive functions such as attention, memory, self-regulation, and executive functioning, which support academic engagement and learning; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_17D2A7E7-D82B-4A7C-B222-A5611DE11D48"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Substantial evidence shows that California’s children and young people are less active than ever. Physical education is an essential academic discipline to develop cognitive, affective, and psychomotor skills that advance their knowledge, and contribute to their dispositions for physical activity at all stages of life; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_EA8E70A6-F53F-469A-8E3D-2A040B8EDA52"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, High-quality instruction in physical education and adapted physical education also makes significant contributions to state priorities, including literacy development, social-emotional learning, school culture, science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM), and others; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_14E56C21-88E6-4DFD-ACBD-F61EFC990FA4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature proclaims May 1, 2026, to May 7, 2026, inclusive, as California Physical Education Week to coincide with National Physical Education and Sport Week, to promote high-quality physical education instruction; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_7A732BAB-7F78-4247-8F01-1EA2EEB7A226"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That all teachers, all school policymakers, and all school leaders be encouraged to provide the highest quality physical education instruction by credentialed physical educators in their schools for all pupils; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_1B7E7BF9-2A91-49A4-93BD-D62C1DF5163D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That California Physical Education Week in 2026 serves as an opportunity for education leaders and state policymakers to collaboratively review current instructional practices in physical education and the need for recommendations to enhance the quality of physical education instruction for all of California’s pupils; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_8A021B93-0446-49F3-98F3-9BC8809225D5"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
